messages.message: I’ve noticed we’re able to import packages to use on AIHub. Is there a referencible list of packages we can import so far

here is a list: https://aihub-uat.internal.instabase.com/docs/aihub-preview/build-custom-function/

I need to ask docs team about when actual docs will become available on prod

Thanks @Eric Han! I see a few missing ones like

```import json
import datetime```
its hard to understand what modules has been implicitly included vs not. Can we work with docs team @jean to get a list of these included too?

I think datetime and json are native to python so they’ll be available. It talks about it in the doc:
```The standard Python library is supported, except for the logging service.```
yep, json and datetime are standard python libraries
@Eric Han Prod docs aren’t published until GA, since they’re public. You can see docs-in-progress at https://aihub-uat.internal.instabase.com/docs/aihub-preview/
@Gwen if there are modules missing, the best thing to do is to create PR to the aihub-docs repo, or, on this particular one, work with @melissa.amos to add them.
oh are docs for all environments hosted from the same place? i.e. uat and prod shares the same docs deployment? Cuz I also couldn’t find custom functions in the uat docs outside of the preview url
Docs aren’t part of the code deployment or environments; they are published completely separately via Wordpress.
Custom functions docs should be in the /docs/aihub-preview/ url but not in the docs/aihub/ URL.
